{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_40","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Project ID validation / active-project path safety**: Reject path-like project IDs before any filesystem lookup or pointer write, and apply the same validation when resolving `active-project`.\n   Current: [`ProjectId::new`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs):263 only trims whitespace, and [`validate_project_exists`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs):104 joins the raw ID directly into the filesystem path. I verified `ralph-burning project select ../escape` and `ralph-burning project select ../../outside` both succeed and persist the traversal string into `.ralph-burning/active-project`.\n   Expected: Only IDs that map to `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/project.toml` should be accepted; separators / traversal segments should fail before selection or resolution.\n   Reference: Spec acceptance criteria for `project select <id>`, `active-project`, and `resolve_active_project(base_dir) -> AppResult<ProjectId>`.\n\n2. **Editor precedence in `config edit`**: Prefer `$EDITOR` before `$VISUAL`.\n   Current: [`open_editor`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs):97 checks `VISUAL` first, then `EDITOR`. A direct probe with both variables set chose the `VISUAL` script, not the `EDITOR` script.\n   Expected: `config edit` should open `workspace.toml` in `$EDITOR`, fall back to `$VISUAL`, then `vi`.\n   Reference: Spec acceptance criterion for `ralph-burning config edit`.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add CLI regression coverage for both rejected path-like project IDs and `$EDITOR` vs `$VISUAL` precedence; the current test suite covers the main happy paths but misses both mismatches."}}
