{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: APPROVED\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Checklist\n- [x] `workspace.toml` now supports `[settings]` with typed `prompt_review.enabled`, `default_flow`, `default_backend`, and `default_model`, while preserving unknown keys on round-trip.\n- [x] `workspace_governance::EffectiveConfig` resolves compiled defaults plus workspace overrides, exposes typed accessors, and is used by the CLI config paths.\n- [x] `config show/get/set/edit` meet the spec: effective values and sources are shown, key/value validation is enforced, edits revalidate after the editor exits, and invalid states fail non-zero.\n- [x] Active-project handling matches the spec: `.ralph-burning/active-project` is the pointer file, `project select <id>` validates existence before writing it, and `resolve_active_project(base_dir)` returns a typed `ProjectId` with clear missing-project messaging.\n- [x] The prior review gaps are fixed: path-like project IDs are rejected before path joins or pointer writes, and `config edit` now prefers `$EDITOR` before `$VISUAL`.\n- [x] Unit, CLI/integration, and Gherkin coverage are present for this slice, and verification passed with `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`.\n\n## Notes\nEvidence is in [src/shared/domain.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs#L263), which now rejects `.` / `..` / `/` / `\\\\` in `ProjectId::new`; [src/adapters/fs.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L35) and [src/adapters/fs.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L97), which keep atomic writes, active-project IO, and editor launch behind the adapter boundary; [src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs#L80), which centralizes effective-config loading and mutation; [src/cli/config.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs#L21) and [src/cli/project.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs#L36), which implement the public commands; and the regression coverage in [tests/unit/config_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/config_test.rs#L16), [tests/unit/active_project_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs#L13), [tests/unit/domain_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs#L31), [tests/cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L134), [tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature#L1), and [tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature#L1).\n\nI also directly probed the fail-fast version behavior: with `version = 999`, both `ralph-burning config show` and `ralph-burning project select alpha` exited non-zero with `unsupported workspace version 999; supported version is 1`, which satisfies the slice’s version-gating requirement.\n\n## Commit Message\nreview: approve slice 3 workspace config and active-project implementation"}}
